---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Bezier Curve Visualiser | Sam Popham" noParticles>
  <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Bezier Curve Visualiser — Deep Dive</h1>

    <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">
      Interactive visualiser demonstrating Bézier curve construction and de
      Casteljau's algorithm with live controls.
    </p>

    <!-- Hero image -->
    <figure class="mb-12">
      <!--
        Image guidance:
        Bezier visualiser full view:
        - control polygon with intermediate construction lines, final curve, and UI slider element,
        - show de Casteljau algorithm in action with colors highlighting different levels.
      -->
      <img
        src="/src/assets/images/deep-dives/bezier/bezier.png"
        alt="Bezier curve visualiser"
        class="w-full rounded-lg shadow-lg"
      />
    </figure>

    <!-- Key features in text-only sections -->
    <div class="space-y-8">
      <article>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">
          Control Points & Construction
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          Step through de Casteljau's algorithm to see how Bézier curves are
          constructed from linear interpolations. The visualiser shows initial
          control polygon, intermediate points and lines for a chosen parameter
          t, with bold colors for the final curve and thinner lines for
          construction steps.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">Parameter Sweep & Animation</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          Animate the parameter t to demonstrate how points move along the curve
          and how intermediate constructions evolve. The slider lets you step
          through any t value and see the construction rebuild in real-time.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">Shader & Render Comparison</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          Compare GPU-rendered output with simple polylines to show smoothing
          and performance benefits. The visualiser can toggle between
          GPU-rendered curves and polyline approximations to highlight
          antialiasing and smoothness improvements.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
>
